President Obama issued a statement on the occasion of Ramadan, extending his best wishes to Muslims in America and around the world. He highlighted the significance of Ramadan as a time for reflection, devotion, and intense prayer. The President emphasized the importance of Muslims' responsibility to one another and to God. He also acknowledged the diversity and contributions of American Muslims to the country. President Obama expressed his anticipation for hosting an Iftar dinner at the White House to celebrate Ramadan and wished Muslims a blessed month.